{"id": "EUVD-2024-54365", "enisaUuid": "c6380235-071d-319f-a0cd-fa16c3a2f4e9", "description": "Net::Xero 0.044 and earlier for Perl uses the rand() function as the default source of entropy, which is not cryptographically secure, for cryptographic functions.\n\nSpecifically Net::Xero uses the Data::Random library which specifically states that it is \"Useful mostly for test programs\". Data::Random uses the rand() function.", "datePublished": "2025-04-05T18:26:22", "dateUpdated": "2025-04-05T18:26:22", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://perldoc.perl.org/functions/rand", "https://security.metacpan.org/docs/guides/random-data-for-security.html", "https://metacpan.org/release/BAREFOOT/Data-Random-0.13/source/lib/Data/Random.pm#L537", "https://metacpan.org/release/ELLIOTT/Net-Xero-0.44/source/lib/Net/Xero.pm#L58", "https://metacpan.org/release/ELLIOTT/Net-Xero-0.44/source/lib/Net/Xero.pm#L9"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-56370"], "assigner": "CPANSec", "epss": 0.08, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "c6427c73-ea5e-3197-9c8f-da8f62cb75d6", "product": {"name": "Net::Xero"}, "product_version": "0 \u22640.44"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "0c6226a7-cca2-330f-a773-b0e505d5e7fc", "vendor": {"name": "ELLIOTT"}}], "isExploited": false}